# WE LOVE MOVIES

A RESTful backend API

## Table of Contents

1. [Overview](#overview)
2. [Technologies Used](#technologies-used)
3. [GitHub](#github)
4. [Install](#install)
5. [Notes](#notes)

## Overview

A RESTful backend ONLY API built with Express, Knex, and PostgreSQL for managing movies, theaters, and reviews.
Deployed on Render as part of the Chegg Skills Capstone final project.

## Technologies Used

1. Node.js + Express

2. Knex.js (SQL query builder)

3. PostgreSQL

4. Jest (testing)

5. Render (for deployment)

## Github

1. Github URL: https://github.com/TiffanyMClark/Final

2. Render URL: https://final-ny55.onrender.com

## Install

1. clone the repo

2. npm i

3. Create an .env file in the root with the following

DB_HOST=localhost

DB_PORT=5432

DB_USER=Your_PSQL_username

DB_PASSWORD=Your_PSQL_password

DB_NAME=postgres

4. npm run reset

5. npm run test

6. npm run start

## Notes

1. This project currently supports local PostgreSQL databases only.

2. Check that your local setup matches the configuration in the Knex file.

3. Render has limited functionality for executing Knex seed files, seeding must be performed locally prior to deployment.
